==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: '''schedule''' ʃεdjul
*[[WEAE]] '''schedule''' skεdjul

===Noun===
'''schedule'''  (''plural:'' '''[[schedules]]''')
# A time-based plan of events. A plan of what is to occur, and at what time it is to occur. A conveyance of such a plan, e.g. a written list.
# An ordered list or table, e.g. a fee schedule.

====Translations====
*Bulgarian: [[расписание]], [[программа]]
*French: [[planning]] ''m'', [[horaire]] ''m''
*German: [[Termin]] (m.), [[Programm]] (n.)
*Japanese: [[予定]]　([[よてい]])
*Russian: [[расписание]], [[программа]]
*Spanish: [[horario]] ''m''
*Turkish: [[program]], [[tarife]]

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|schedul|e}}
# To create a schedule.
# To add a meeting, appointment or event to one's personal schedule.
#:''I'll '''schedule''' you for three-o'clock then.''

====Translations====
*French: [[planifier]] (1)

